This article discusses Executive Order 13554, which establishes the Gulf Coast Ecosystem Restoration Task Force. The purpose of this task force is to coordinate intergovernmental efforts to restore and conserve the Gulf Coast ecosystem, which is important for the economy, environment, and culture of the region. The task force consists of representatives from various executive departments and agencies, as well as state representatives and potentially representatives from affected tribes. The task force will develop a Gulf of Mexico Regional Ecosystem Restoration Strategy, propose ecosystem restoration goals, and coordinate research and monitoring efforts. The order also outlines the administration and functions of the task force.